   Dividend News:
   Community National
   Bancorp Sets Payout,
   Its First in 14 Years
</HL>
<DATE>
06/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10
</SO>
<CO>
   CNB
</CO>
<IN>
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Community National Bancorp Inc. directors
declared a 5% stock dividend, the first payout in 14 years by
the Staten Island, N.Y., holding company for Community
National Bank &amp; Trust Co. of New York.
   The dividend is payable July 25 to stock of record July 3.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   At the annual meeting, Community National shareholders
also approved a proposal to reduce authorized shares to 15
million from 50 million. The move will reduce the franchise
tax the bank pays in Delaware, where it is incorporated; the
tax is partly based on the number of shares a company is
authorized to issue. The cut in authorized shares doesn't
affect shares outstanding. Community National has around
three million shares outstanding.
   The bank reiterated that second-quarter earnings will drop
from the year-ago period but that it is hoping for an upturn
in the second half.
   In the first quarter, net income fell 73% to $211,000, or
seven cents a share, from $793,000, or 30 cents a share, a
year earlier. The bank's provision for possible losses on bad
loans grew to $1.3 million from $200,000. Assets climbed 32%
to $408 million.
   In American Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,
Community National shares rose 25 cents to $6.75.
</TEXT>
