<HL>
   Raw-Steel Production
   Increased 1% in Week
</HL>
<DATE>
06/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15
</SO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Raw-steel production by the nation's mills
increased 1% last week to 1,893,000 tons from 1,875,000 tons
the previous week, the American Iron and Steel Institute
said.
   Last week's output rose 0.3% from the 1,887,000 tons
produced a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The industry used 84.2% of its capability last week,
compared with 83.4% the previous week and 85.3% a year ago.
   The American Iron and Steel Institute reported:
                                                                                                       

                               Net tons     Capability
                               produced    utilization
                                                                                                       

 Week to June 23 ............  1,893,000       84.2
 Week to June 16 ............  1,875,000       83.4
 Year to date ............... 47,477,000       85.1
 Year earlier to date ....... 39,300,000       89.2
                                                                                                       

   The capability utilization rate is a calculation designed
to indicate at what percent of its production capability the
industry is operating in a given week.
</TEXT>
