<LP>
   CHEVRON Corp. (San Francisco) -- The company's Chevron
U.S.A. Inc. subsidiary named seven vice president/general
managers to head new business units for exploration, land and
production.
   The positions were created as part of a restructuring of
the domestic oil and natural gas subsidiary, based in San
Francisco. John Cameron, vice president of the western
region, was named vice president, western production business
unit. Gene Thomas, manager of the Denver division of western
region production, becomes vice president, Rocky Mountain
production business unit. Jim Hooks, general manager,
exploration, for the eastern region, becomes vice president,
western exploration business unit. Will Lewis, general
manager of production in the central region, becomes vice
president, central production business unit. Burt
Branstetter, regional counsel in Chevron U.S.A.'s law
department, becomes vice president, land business unit. Bob
Herrin Jr., vice president of manufacturing for Warren
Petroleum Co., a Chevron subsidiary, becomes vice president,
Permian Basin production business unit. Dave Lott Jr.,
general manager of exploration and land at the Chevron U.S.A.
headquarters staff, becomes vice president, eastern
exploration business unit. The appointments are effective
Aug. 1.
