BROADLINE RETAILERS, DEPARTMENT STORES (RTB)
</IN>
<LP>
   Dayton Hudson Corp., Minneapolis, said it plans to dismiss
about 850 central-office employees of Chicago-based Marshall
Field &amp; Co. by the end of the year.
   Last week, Dayton Hudson completed its acquisition of the
upscale retailing chain from B.A.T Industries PLC of Britain
for $1.05 billion.
</LP>
