<HL>
   International Brief -- Sankyo Co.:
   Consolidated Pretax Profit
   Rose 1.4% for Fiscal Year
</HL>
<DATE>
06/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A14
</SO>
<CO>
   J.SKY
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Sankyo Co., a major Japanese pharmaceutical maker, said
its consolidated pretax profit for the year ended March 31
rose 1.4%, to 36.16 billion yen ($233.4 million) from 35.67
billion yen a year earlier.
   Net income declined 7.9% to 13.02 billion yen from 14.13
billion yen, after paying a larger amount of taxes due to
extraordinary profits caused by the disposition of reserves
for retirement allowances. As a result, per-share net fell to
36.41 yen from 39.89 yen.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sales were down slightly at 425.63 billion yen from 426.04
billion yen.
   Sales of agrichemicals dropped 10.9% to 39.17 billion yen,
affected by the government's continuing policy to cut the
number of rice fields.
   Sales of pharmaceuticals posted a 1.2% increase, to 282.22
billion yen, while those of foodstuffs inched up 1.6% to
48.79 billion yen.
   Sankyo predicted consolidated pretax profit of 40 billion
yen for next year, with expected net income of 18 billion
yen. Sales were projected at 440 billion yen.
</TEXT>
