<HL>
   Business Brief -- One Bancorp:
   Maine Savings Bank Unit
   Plans to Sell Branch Offices
</HL>
<DATE>
06/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11
</SO>
<CO>
   TONE BKB PHBK
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<LP>
   Maine Savings Bank, a unit of One Bancorp, said it signed
agreements in principle for the sale of its Bath and Camden
banking offices to Casco Northern Bank, a unit of Bank of
Boston Corp.
   Maine Savings, based in Portland, also agreed in principle
to sell four other offices -- its Brewer, Bucksport and North
Windham offices to Peoples Heritage Bank, and its South Paris
office to Androscoggin Savings Bank.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Terms weren't disclosed and all sales require regulatory
approval. The transactions are expected to be completed
before year's end, Maine Savings said, and would reduce the
bank's assets by $180 million to about $1.5 billion.
   Maine Savings withdrew plans to sell five other offices
offered in January that didn't sell, Bangor Mall, Bangor Main
Street, Orono, Old Town and Waterville.
</TEXT>
